@@ -77,15 +77,17 @@
 npm run speech:install-hmong
 ```
 
-For Raspberry Pi read-aloud support, also install the lightweight local speech package:
-
-```bash
-sudo apt-get install -y espeak-ng
-```
-
-This gives the kiosk a server-side voice fallback when Chromium says read aloud is not available in
-the browser. English, Spanish fallback, and Somali can use this package. Hmong still uses the
-separate Hmong phrase or fallback voice setup.
+For Raspberry Pi read-aloud support, install the natural voice tools plus the lightweight emergency
+fallback:
+
+```bash
+sudo apt-get install -y espeak-ng python3-pip
+python3 -m pip install --user --break-system-packages --upgrade edge-tts gTTS
+```
+
+English uses `edge-tts` first for a smoother voice. Spanish and Somali use cloud speech when the Pi
+has internet. `espeak-ng` remains installed only as the emergency fallback. Hmong tries cloud speech
+and still uses the separate Hmong phrase or fallback voice setup when available.
 
